{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idee57a201-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s902"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"902"},"text":"§ 902.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" General authority of Secretary of Agriculture","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idee57a202-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s902/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Loans","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of Agriculture (referred to in this chapter as the “Secretary”) is authorized and empowered to make loans, or refinance loans made or guaranteed by the Secretary under this chapter, in the several States and Territories of the United States for rural electrification and for the purpose of furnishing and improving electric and telephone service in rural areas, as provided in this chapter, and for the purpose of assisting electric borrowers to implement demand side management, energy efficiency and conservation programs, and on-grid and off-grid renewable energy systems.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idee57a203-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s902/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Investigations and reports","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary may make, or cause to be made, studies, investigations, and reports regarding matters, including financial, technological, and regulatory matters, affecting the condition and progress of electric, telecommunications, and economic development in rural areas, and publish and disseminate information with respect to the matters.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idee57a204-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s902/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Technical assistance","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 180 days after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-12-20"},"text":"December 20, 2018","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary shall enter into a memorandum of understanding with the Secretary of Energy under which the Secretary of Energy shall provide technical assistance to the Rural Utilities Service on loans to be made under subsection (a) of this section and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s904/a"},"text":"section 904(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idee57a205-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1936-05-20/ch432"},"text":"May 20, 1936, ch. 432","children":[],"tail":", title I, § 2, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/1363"},"text":"49 Stat. 1363","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-10-28/ch776"},"text":"Oct. 28, 1949, ch. 776","children":[],"tail":", §§ 2, 3, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/948"},"text":"63 Stat. 948","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/129/s2/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–129, § 2(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-11-01"},"text":"Nov. 1, 1993","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/107/1363"},"text":"107 Stat. 1363","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/354/tII/s235/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–354, title II, § 235(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (13), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/3220"},"text":"108 Stat. 3220","children":[],"tail":", 3221; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/127/tVII/s771"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–127, title VII, § 771","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-04-04"},"text":"Apr. 4, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/1149"},"text":"110 Stat. 1149","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/234/tVI/s6101"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–234, title VI, § 6101","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-05-22"},"text":"May 22, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/1195"},"text":"122 Stat. 1195","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/246/s4/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–246, § 4(a)","children":[],"tail":", title VI, § 6101, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-06-18"},"text":"June 18, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/1664"},"text":"122 Stat. 1664","children":[],"tail":", 1956; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/tVI/s6501"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, title VI, § 6501","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/4771"},"text":"132 Stat. 4771","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/94/dB/tVII/s765"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–94, div. B, title VII, § 765","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2019-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 2019","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/133/2655"},"text":"133 Stat. 2655","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idee57a206-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idee57a207-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idee57a208-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/234"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–234","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/246"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–246","children":[],"tail":" made identical amendments to this section. The amendments by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/234"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–234","children":[],"tail":" were repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/246/s4/a"},"text":"section 4(a) of Pub. L. 110–246","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idee57a209-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2019—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/94"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–94","children":[],"tail":" substituted “made or guaranteed by the Secretary” for “made by the Secretary”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/s6501/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, § 6501(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “loans, or refinance loans made by the Secretary under this chapter, in” for “loans in”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/s6501/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, § 6501(b)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (c)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/246/s6101"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–246, § 6101","children":[],"tail":", inserted “efficiency and” before “conservation”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/127/s771/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–127, § 771(1)","children":[],"tail":", inserted section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/127/s771/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–127, § 771(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), inserted heading, substituted “The Secretary of Agriculture (referred to in this chapter as the ‘Secretary’) is” for “The Secretary of Agriculture is”, struck out “and the furnishing of electric energy to persons in rural areas who are not receiving central station service” after “rural electrification”, and substituted “systems.” for “systems; to make, or cause to be made, studies, investigations, and reports concerning the condition and progress of the electrification of and the furnishing of adequate telephone service in rural areas in the several States and Territories; and to publish and disseminate information with respect thereto.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/127/s771/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–127, § 771(3)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (b) and struck out former subsec. (b) which read as follows: “By "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 1994","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary shall issue interim regulations to implement the authority contained in subsection (a) of this section to make loans for the purpose of assisting electric borrowers to implement demand side management, energy conservation programs, and on-grid and off-grid renewable energy systems. If the regulations are not issued by "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 1994","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary shall consider any demand side management, energy conservation, or renewable energy program, system, or activity that is approved by a State agency to be eligible for the loans.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/354"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–354","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Secretary of Agriculture” for “Administrator” in subsec. (a) and “Secretary” for “Administrator” in two places in subsec. (b)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1993—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/129"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–129","children":[],"tail":" designated existing provisions as subsec. (a), substituted “electric and telephone service in rural areas, as provided in this chapter, and for the purpose of assisting electric borrowers to implement demand side management, energy conservation programs, and on-grid and off-grid renewable energy systems;” for “telephone service in rural areas, as hereinafter provided;”, and added subsec. (b)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1949—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 1949","children":[],"tail":", authorized loans to furnish and improve rural telephone service; and inserted “title I,” in credit of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1936-05-20"},"text":"May 20, 1936","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idee57a20a-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idee57a20b-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2008 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment of this section and repeal of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/234"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–234","children":[],"tail":" by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/246"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–246","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-05-22"},"text":"May 22, 2008","children":[],"tail":", the date of enactment of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/234"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–234","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/246/s4"},"text":"section 4 of Pub. L. 110–246","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s8701"},"text":"section 8701 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
